gif" align=absmiddle>  Mid range 1st time, main char, dwarf war upgrade advice/sug.</span><hr size=1> Ok, 3rd time has to be the charm to get this post to work.<br>
<br>
This is my main and only &quot;high&quot; lev char being a dwarf warrior lev 36 on Fennin Ro.  Just joined a guild that doesnt have too many high levs that can donate items or plat though I have a decient set of mismatched armor for a non twink &lt;I think&gt; and have now gotten up to having about 10k plat to spend on some nice upgrades and I needed some advice<br>
<br>
&lt;Sorry if this seems a bit reptitive, but most of the posts I have read apply to you super level 50+ warriors and all that info is way out of my league right now&gt;<br>
<br>
1st here is my magelo profile I hope, if I figure out how to link it correctly <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=553907">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=553907</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
1. Weapons, I currently use a wurmy and a cent short sword and know that soon &lt;early 40's&gt; my wurmy will loose its punch compared to other fairly cheap weps. <br>
I have seen a few posts about offhanding a velium swiftblade because of the great haste, how good, and how long would a wurmy/swiftblade comb be viable or what might be some other options.<br>
<br>
From the bazaar prices I can get a lamentation and/or a Centi Longsword fairly inexpensivly...or what other choices might be good based on my level and money onhand.<br>
<br>
2. Armor- From the posts it looks like a haste item is overdue...again from bazaar prices it looks like I could get a fbss, schw or maybe a sash of the dragon born &lt;though this would eat up much more of my funds and might not be the best overall value choice&gt;.  I like the look, stats and somewhat price of the schw at 3000ish...but I am the lukcy owner of some nice cobalt gauntlets &lt;which is my highest AC item right now&gt;.  <br>
<br>
So I guess my 2A question is: do you think the speed/stats of the schw and the ablilty to use a better belt item &lt;currently spider fur&gt; offsets taking my 25ac gauntlets off for?<br>
<br>
And 2b question: what other semi inexpensive upgrades to my armour would be suitible for my current situation...some things I have looked at getting are a better BP &lt;either barbed ringmail or a nice dwarven plate piece, both 30ac up from my crafted 22&gt; maybe a dwarven helm for 400ish, a dwarven boots for 600ish, maybe even the dwarven greeves and vambraces of which I dont recall the price right now.<br>
<br>
Or any other possibilities or advice you all have.  Thank you in advance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/14/03 3:04:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4846.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mid range 1st time, main char, dwarf war upgrade advice/</span><hr size=1> As far as weapons:  When you hit about 45, then you'll want to ditch the Wurmy for a Lammy.  The Centi SS is an ok off hand, but if you could upgrade that to the Centi LS, that might be a bit better.  When you hit 40, try to get a Frostbringer, can't beat the agro/pp equiation for it =)<br>
<br>
Definaly get haste if you can, SCHW or FBSS, or whatever you can.  There have been many debates on how good of a combo a SCHW/belt better than Spider Fur Versus Cobalt Gaunts/FBSS, but it's a toss up.  One is cheaper, one has more stats, etc.  So that would be up to you.<br>
<br>
For armor, crusty greeves will be a big improvement over your crafted greeves.  Or if you can get more of the dwarf cultural, then go for that as well.  Cobalt arms should be pretty cheap as well now, and would sever you better with 12 more raw AC than the Black Ice.  Barbed Ringmail would be a great upgrade over your crafted BP.<br>
<br>
And always, when you get to planar level, the old Plane of Hate armor is pretty good until you can replace it with some kind of velious quest gear.<br>
