</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roughbeard>Roughbeard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/14/03 3:12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4846.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mid range 1st time, main char, dwarf war upgrade advice/</span><hr size=1> The Dwarvish armor is really nice for the price. Barbed Ringmail for Chest, Get a haste item (Fbss or SCHW, avoid Sotbd) Might suggest buying SCHW and then getting a Axgorath's Belt from ME, rots all the time. or stick with fbss + cobalt guants. For weps, soon it will be time to get rid of the wurmy, look for a lammy and another wep. the best bang for your buck wep imho is frostbringer. you wont be able to afford the frosty but look forward to it in the future. <br>
<br>
Barbed Ringmail - 1.5-2k<br>
fbss - 1-2k<br>
schw - 2k<br>
Lammy - 1.5k<br>
Dwarven Plate Armor - dont know prices, probly a couple hundred a piece<br>
Ancient Seahorse Hide Cloak - 1k<br>
Maybe some Acrylia Plate Armor<br>
Cobalt Arms - 1k<br>
*Frostbringer - 4-5k<br>
*Sebilite Croaking Dirk - 3k-4k<br>
<br>
<br>
(* = you wont be able to afford the item but look forward to it in the future)<br>
<br>
Would suggest going with a lammy/lammy combo, schw, and dwarven plate armor, the cloak (nice ac + 25hp), maybe mix some acrylia plate in there. you will be fine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
