<br>
Cobalt arms and boots for 2800 total!<br>
Dwarven plate breastplate and greeves for 3000 total<br>
and a FBSS for 1500<br>
<br>
So now I think I look like this if I put everything in correctly:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=553907">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=553907</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I think next to buy will be a centi longsword, maybe a dwarven plate helm...and save buying a lammy untill I get to the low 40's.<br>
<br>
From the looks of things what would anyone suggest for additional armor or weapons at level 36ish with not much plat left. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/03 3:02:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4846.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Upgrades so far</span><hr size=1> You look remarkably like I looked.  Definitely Centi LS for the off hand, Lammy if you must, but you may as well look for Defiance.<br>
<br>
Personally, I was satisfied going Jagged Blade of Mourning/Centi LS off up until 45 when I went to a Black Acrylia Halberd.  My personal oppinion based on the numbers I ran, is once hasted the Lammy doesn't outdamage the superior ratio of the Jagged until at least 45, and then perhaps just barely.  I went to the BAH then, though, and to a Windblade from there.<br>
<br>
